review: Dr. Sitaram examined my dental problems and patiently explained various treatment options that are specific to my issues. dear karthik
 to do scaling i have to do sterilization and maintain a clean and healthy environment for which i have to charge you. you mentioned your relatives have undergone for scaling for rs. 300/- did they have sterilization pouches for the instruments? is the doctor a periodontist with 14 years experience?? there are many things to consider before coming to a conclusion.

tags: Explanation of the health issue,Doctor friendliness,Wait time,
review: I had broken teeth due to which food was directly pressing gums and was very painful. I went to another dentist earlier. He did the filling and suggested that if the filling is broken we need to go for the cap. Then I wanted to go to more experienced doctor as I dont want to go for cap yet. I found Dr Seetharam through Practo. Dr Seetharaman had suggested not to go for cap yet but to go for filling leaving slight GAP between the broken teeth and the adjacent one, and see if works. Filling is done with GAP but within 3 months the filling is broken. I met Mr. Seetharam again after 3 months but this time another doctor (Tejaswi) has done the filling without GAP. Dr. Seetharam suggested that the filling lasts 1 yr max (in my case its just 3 months). We usually try filling twice and then will go for rootcanal + cap after that.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review: Hello everyoneThis is TejaI am really glad to share my experience about Dr Sunitha as well Dr Seetharam.Well coming to my problem ...My tooth on left upper jaw  got fractured five years back and the situation of that is it have to be removed actually,but I am so fortunate enough that Dr Sunita saved my tooth by RCT ...I am so so thankful to her.And recently during this pandemic ,the other tooth on the right upper jaw got fractured,this time they couldn't save the tooth since the fracture extended to root,but they were so kind enough to do the treatment during this pandemic .They have extracted my tooth with the help of some other specialist and placed an implant too. They have took utmost care. Before the treatment it was so painful for me while chewing that side but now everything is super fine.Thanks to both the doctors for their hard work and utmost careBy God's grace I am in hands of good dental doctors,so no worries about my teeth

review: To remove tooth he was in hurry and should have wait for more time after anesthesia ***** ** *** *** ***** *********. After removal of tooth with huge pain we felt that anesthesia start working.
reply_text: Dear sandeep after anesthesia we waited for 15 minutes and also we have given a second dose of anesthesia and again waited. Once we have confirmed that anesthesia is acting then only we start removal.
